public class WrappingEObjectImpl
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.impl.EObjectImpl
implements cn.edu.pku.sei.ra.wrapping.CommonWrapping.WrappingEObject

An implementation of the model object 'Wrapping EObject'.

This is the super class of every *Impl Class generated by SandTablist Framework, Some of its methods are the so called "hook" methods. Subsequent developers need to overwrite some of these hook classes with the code specific to the objective management capability. From this perspective, these hook classes is the bridge between the common MOF reflection like interface and the platform specific operation method.

Every instance of WrappingEObject (or sub Classes) contain a "core" indicating a unique manageable element in the running system. Most of the operations, like life- cycle control, getting/setting attributes or references are executed using this core.

This is the list of all the hook methods

  • look up a core
  • create a core
  • destroy a core
  • add sub core for a containment reference
  • remove a sub core for a containment reference
  • list a set of sub cores for a containment reference
  • look up the proper EClass for a sub core
  • check matching with another core object
  • add a value into a multi-valued attribute
  • remove a value from a multi-valued attribute

addSubCore

public boolean addSubCore(cn.edu.pku.sei.ra.wrapping.CommonWrapping.WrappingEObject wrappingEObject,
                          int featureID)
HOOK!

add a sub core into the proper location after the wrappingEObject has been added into a multi-valued reference

switch(featureID){ case XxxPackage.XXX__XXX1: //get the list of cores for XXX__XXX1 reference break; case XxxPackage.XXX__XXX2: //get the list of cores for XXX__XXX2 reference break; ... }

it is possible that you call addSubCore, but the sub WrappingEObject do not have a core yet, and you may wish to re-add it later automatically. if you need this help, remember to add if(!super.addSubCore(wrappingEObject,featureID)) return false; in the front of the rewritten implementation.

need to rewrite ONLY IF this WrappingEObject has multi-valued references, and this references need to be changed though the model side.

Specified by:
addSubCore in interface cn.edu.pku.sei.ra.wrapping.CommonWrapping.WrappingEObject
Parameters:
wrappingEObject: - the sub wrappingEObject to add
featureID: - the reference's feature id
Returns:
if the add operation has been executed successfully

getChildClassMap

public org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EClass getChildClassMap(java.lang.Object object)
get the proper EClass for the WrappingEObject to wrap a manageable element indicated by parameter "object".

usually in a format like switch(featureID){ case XxxPackage.XXX__XXX1: if(SomeCondition(object)) return XXXPackage.eINSTANCE.getSomeEClass(); break; ... }

need to rewrite ONLY IF the type of some reference is an abstract EClass.
